   <abstract >In 1870, Sloop Walker leaves his home to live and work in the oil-bearing region of northwestern Pennsylvania referred to as Petrolia. After becoming involved with a local eccentric known only as the Baron, Sloop arrives in the fictional town of Earth Circuit, where a crew of seasoned rig-builders initiates him into the peculiar and transient lifestyle of the workers transforming Pennsylvaniaâ€™s forests into centers of industry. But when Sloop encounters an underground network of revolutionary agents, he begins to view his labor in the forests of Petrolia as trespass against a sacred space. Inspired by history and theory alike, Petrolia examines an America haunted by its rapid expansion and conjures a landscape teetering on the edge of both radical progress and utter collapse.</abstract>
